verbose_text: In CGNs, the Akt / mTOR pathway, which is activated by neuritin, is known to up-regulate Kv4.2 gene transcription, resulting in an increase in the I A densities, which is also associated with the development and maturation of CGNs [XREF_BIBR].
evidence: mTOR pathway, which is activated by neuritin, is known to up-regulate Kv4.2 gene transcription
